text.tspan: A SAMD21 Development board with LoRaWAN

svg.text: VDDIO: Powers I/O lines, OSC8M and XOSC. Voltage is 1.62V to 3.63V
VDDANA: Powers I/O lines and the ADC, AC, DAC, PTC,OSCULP32K, OSC32K, XOSC32K. Voltage is 1.62V to 3.63V.

text.tspan: The SAMDaaNo21 is based on the ATSAMD21G18 with a Arduino NANO form factor and LoRaWAN.
* Six serial communication modules (SERCOM) configurable as: UART/USART, SPI or I2C
* Full Speed USB Device and embedded Host
* Support for up to 120 touch channels
* Easy pin migration to SAMD21G and SAMD21J devices
